## Cycle Plan

```yaml
- id: C1
  goal: <human-readable cycle goal — e.g. "implement the user storage layer">
  files_affected:
    - src/storage/users.ts
    - src/storage/types.ts
  acceptance: [AC-001]
  goal_condition: |
    cycles/C1/result.json exists with status: pass AND
    cycles/C1/review.md has 0 critical clusters,
    or stop after 30 turns

- id: C2
  goal: <…>
  files_affected: [<…>]
  acceptance: [AC-002]
  goal_condition: |
    cycles/C2/result.json exists with status: pass AND
    cycles/C2/review.md has 0 critical clusters,
    or stop after 30 turns

- id: C3
  goal: <final cycle — includes e2e wiring>
  files_affected: [<…>]
  acceptance: [AC-003]
  e2e_covers: [E-001, E-002]
  goal_condition: |
    cycles/C3/result.json exists with status: pass AND
    cycles/C3/review.md has 0 critical clusters AND
    e2e scenarios E-001, E-002 are exercised by tests in this cycle,
    or stop after 30 turns
```

> Cycles run **sequentially**. The outer goal session reads this block,
> picks the next pending cycle, and spawns one `claude -p` child per
> cycle.

## Reviewer Config

```yaml
model: opus            # or sonnet
dimensions:
  - correctness        # ★ default
  - simplicity         # ★ default
  - security           # ★ default
  # additional Tier 1: design, error-handling, tests-vs-impl
  # Tier 2: performance, naming-readability, dependency-hygiene,
  #         type-safety, concurrency, observability
  # Tier 3 (declare per-project as needed):
  #         sui-move-idioms, frontend-a11y, api-contract-stability
```

- The **length of `dimensions`** = number of reviewers dispatched per
  cycle.
- Want 2 security reviewers? List `security` twice.
- `model` is passed through to each reviewer's `Agent` dispatch.

## Worker Config

> **Optional block.** Absent => `count: 6, hinted_workers: 0`, which is
> identical to pre-FACF behavior (every best-of-N worker pristine, every
> round). See `docs/failed-approaches-carryforward.md`.

```yaml
count: 6            # best-of-N implementer pool size per cycle
hinted_workers: 0   # of `count`, how many receive cycles/<id>/failures.md
                    # on a RETRY round (round >= 2). 0 = always pristine.
```

- `count` was previously the implicit "default 6".
- `hinted_workers` only takes effect on **retry** rounds — round 1 has no
  failures yet, so all workers are pristine regardless.
- Constraint: `hinted_workers < count` (always keep >= 1 pristine worker,
  or the pool re-correlates and the carry-forward defeats itself).

